main event: An airline reported sighting a round bright object over the Pacific Ocean on December 16, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to change size and seemed to fade in and out of observation., The observers noted long contrails extending from the object., The sighting lasted for approximately 3 minutes., The report indicates possible multiple distant objects breaking into formation., Conclusion drawn from insufficient data regarding the nature of the object.
sighted object: one round bright object with contrails
